<!doctype html><html><head><meta charset="utf-8"><title>H38-T008 Custom Work Build</title><style>body{font-family:Arial,sans-serif;line-height:1.45;color:#111827}h1{color:#0f172a}h2{border-bottom:1px solid #cbd5e1}table{border-collapse:collapse;width:100%;margin:12px 0}td,th{border:1px solid #cbd5e1;padding:8px}th{background:#e2e8f0}.note{background:#f8fafc;border-left:5px solid #f97316;padding:10px}</style></head><body><h1>Highway 38 Solutions - Custom Work Build</h1><p><b>Sample ID:</b> H38-T008<br><b>Scenario:</b> Repeat job math to version-one internal tracker</p><p><img src="../assets/sample-custom-work-proof.svg" style="width:100%;max-width:760px"></p><h2>Customer input</h2><ul><li>Owner repeats the same estimate math for small jobs.</li><li>Inputs: size, material, labor hours, trip cost, options, and notes.</li><li>Problem: quotes depend on memory and old text messages.</li><li>Goal: version-one tracker that works on sample rows.</li></ul><h2>Version-one scope</h2><table><tr><th>Included</th><th>Not included</th></tr><tr><td>Input fields, quote range, assumptions, notes, simple handoff SOP.</td><td>Payment processing, accounting sync, legal contract wording, unlimited revisions.</td></tr><tr><td>Five sample test rows and one owner checklist.</td><td>Full app, customer portal, or automatic invoicing.</td></tr></table><h2>Build logic</h2><table><tr><th>Input</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Output</th></tr><tr><td>Job size</td><td>Scale material/labor</td><td>Base range</td></tr><tr><td>Material group</td><td>Estimate cost category</td><td>Material allowance</td></tr><tr><td>Labor hours</td><td>Estimate effort</td><td>Labor line</td></tr><tr><td>Options</td><td>Add choices</td><td>Good/better/best quote</td></tr></table><div class="note"><b>Definition of done:</b> Version one works on sample rows, has clear boundaries, and gives the owner a repeatable quoting starting point.</div></body></html>